OL,3,C'Two-tier justice': Why are the
OL,4,Cgovernment and the Sentencing Council
OL,5,Cclashing?
OL,7,FThe chairman said: "Any judge or
OL,8,Fmagistrate required to sentence an
OL,9,Foffender must do all that they can to
OL,10,Favoid a difference in outcome based on
OL,11,Fethnicity.
OL,13,F"The judge will be better equipped to
OL,14,Fdo that if they have as much
OL,15,Finformation as possible about the
OL,16,Foffender. The cohort of ethnic,
OL,17,Fcultural and faith minority groups may
OL,18,Fbe a cohort about which judges and
OL,19,Fmagistrates are less well informed."
